===Etymology===
From Irish ''[[bean#Irish|bean]] [[sídhe]]'' (Old Irish ''[[ben]] [[síde]]'') literally ‘woman of the fairy mound’.  The term ''banshee'' entered English in 1771.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/bænˈʃi:/, /ˈbænʃi:/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# In Irish folklore, a female spirit, usually taking the form of a woman whose mournful wailing warns of an impending death.

